TSClang is an original compiler that transpiles a TypeScript-inspired language
(.tsc) to C. It does not use, copy, or incorporate any source code from the
TypeScript compiler (https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript).

The input language syntax is inspired by TypeScript, which is developed by
Microsoft and licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
TypeScript is a trademark of Microsoft Corporation.
